Description: Handle, handle plate, and body sherd of East Greek grey ware large pottery column-krater; dark grey fabric core sandwiched between grey-buff margins; numerous mica inclusions; worn dark grey slip on handle plate and on exterior.
Curator's comments: For a similar handle from Larisa, see Boehlau and Schefold, ‘Larisa am Hermos, 1902-34 - II: Die Kleinfunde’, (1942), pl. 46, no. 12.
Probably from the same krater as 1924,1201.65.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.034)
